---
<Base title={title}>
  <Sidebar />
  <main class="page-main">
    <h1 class="page-title">The TRGB-SBF Project. IV. TRGB Color Calibration in JWST F090W+F150W</h1>

    <div class="infobox">
      <h3 class="infobox-title">Chazov et al. (2026)</h3>
      <table>
        <tr>
          <th>Type:</th>
          <td>Paper</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th>Authors:</th>
          <td>M. I. Chazov, D. I. Makarov, R. B. Tully, G. S. Anand, L. N. Makarova, Y. Cohen, J. P. Blakeslee, M. Cantiello, J. B. Jensen, G. Raimondo</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th>arXiv / DOI:</th>
          <td><a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.11160">arXiv:2603.11160</a> — <a href="https://doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2603.11160">DOI</a></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th>Date:</th>
          <td>2026-03-11 (v1) — ApJ accepted</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th>Analysis:</th>
          <td><a href="/data/papers/chazov2026_trgb_jwst_calibration.md">Paper analysis (markdown)</a></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <th>Related concepts:</th>
          <td>
            <WikiLink slug="pages/trgb_distance_indicator" text="TRGB distance method" /><br>
            <WikiLink slug="pages/distance_ladder" text="Distance ladder" />
          </td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </div>

    <p><strong>Abstract (short)</strong> — Chazov et al. calibrate the tip of the red giant branch (TRGB) in JWST F090W using 17 nearby galaxies. They find M_F090W^TRGB = -4.40 ± 0.03 mag (Vega) at low metallicities, with a transition to fainter magnitudes at (F090W-F150W)_0 > 1.65 mag. NGC 4258 maser distance anchors the zero point; revised distances are ~1.5% smaller than prior values.</p>

    <h2 id="key-findings">Key findings</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
        TRGB absolute magnitude in F090W is constant at M = -4.40 ± 0.03 mag for (F090W-F150W)₀ &lt; 1.65 mag.  
        <small><a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.11160">(Chazov et al. 2026, arXiv:2603.11160)</a></small>
      </li>
      <li>
        TRGB magnitude declines at higher metallicities; the break at (F090W-F150W)₀ ≃ 1.65 mag corresponds to [M/H] ≃ -0.57 (10 Gyr isochrones).  
        <small>(Chazov+2026)</small>
      </li>
      <li>
        Revised distance moduli are ~1.5% smaller (Δμ ≃ -0.03 mag) than previously published values, driven by updated JWST calibrations.  
        <small>(Chazov+2026)</small>
      </li>
      <li>
        New RGB color-slicing methodology enables precise TRGB detection across metallicity ranges, improving the Population II distance ladder.  
        <small>(Chazov+2026)</small>
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h2 id="methods">Methods</h2>
    <p>The authors apply maximum likelihood estimation (MLE) to RGB luminosity functions measured in color-sliced color-magnitude diagrams. Each galaxy's F090W vs (F090W-F150W) CMD is segmented into narrow color strips; within each, they fit a broken power-law RGB model to identify the TRGB magnitude. NGC 4258 (geometric maser distance μ = 29.397 ± 0.032 mag) sets the absolute calibration; remaining 16 galaxies determine the color-dependent relation.</p>

    <h2 id="implications">Implications</h2>
    <p>
      This work refines the Population II rung of the cosmic distance ladder, enabling more precise measurements of the Hubble constant. The color-aware TRGB calibration is critical for leveraging JWST observations of intermediate-to-high metallicity stellar populations in nearby galaxy clusters and beyond.
    </p>

